# POPULAR TRING METHODS & OTHER FUNCTIONS
# https://docs.python.org/3/library - Python Standard Library
#
# FUNCITONS
# type() - gives type in format '<type type_name>'
# type()__name__ - just returns 'type_name'
# id() - returns location in memory of object
# dir() - returns a list of methods available to an object
#
# METHODS
# len() - returns number of characters in a string
# capitalize() - capitalizes the first character in a string
# upper() - returns uppercase of every letter
# lower() - returns lowercase of every letter
# strip() - removes whitespace SURROUNDING a string
# find() - returns index of what you're looking for; indexOf() in java
# split() - returns a list object of all the strings separated by a space; can change delimiter using a param
# join() - inverse of split; USAGE: delimiter.join(list_name) e.g. ' '.join(list_name) for a space delimiter
# import string - module that gives access to kool stuff
#
# DIFFERENCE BETWEEN FUNCTIONS AND METHODS
# Functions are independent of a class and use a notation function_name(param)
# Methods are functions that belong to a certain class and use dot notation e.g. object_name.function_name(param)
